						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up opposite to the temple of Vēṇugōpālasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1544, Durmati, Phālguṇa, śu. 3.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Mentions Parāśarakēsari and Sudarśana and records the obeisance to Śiṅgarāchārya, the <hi rend="italic">Purōhita</hi> of god Raṅganātha (temple). Seems to register gifts made to the god Gōpālasvāmi and to the images of Ramānuja and Nammāḷvar.</p>						

						</summary>
